properties.headline: Air Quality Alert issued January 4 at 2:00AM MST by NWS Rapid City SD
properties.description:
Southwest winds will increase this morning and gusty winds will
continue into this evening. Wind speeds will reach 25 to 40 mph,
with gusts as high as 50 mph. The wind will begin to decrease late
this evening.

The Wyoming Air Quality Division recommends the elderly, young
children, and individuals with respiratory problems avoid
excessive physical exertion and minimize outdoor activities during
this time. Although these people are most susceptible to health
impacts, the air quality division also advises that everyone
should avoid prolonged exposure to the poor air quality
conditions.

NWSheadline: BLOWING DUST HEALTH ALERT IN EFFECT FOR THE POWDER RIVER BASIN OF NORTHEASTERN WYOMING FROM 9 AM MDT TODAY UNTIL 10 PM MDT
